      <header>
        <div class="logo-badge" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div>
          <h1>Privacy Policy – Taptale</h1>
          <p class="meta">
            Last updated: 03/12/2025 &nbsp;•&nbsp; Application: <strong>Taptale</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
      </header>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Taptale</strong> (“the App”, “we”, “our”) collects, uses, and protects
        user information. By using the App, you agree to the practices described in this document.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

      <h3>1.1. Non-personal information (collected automatically)</h3>
      <p>
        Taptale may automatically collect non-identifiable data necessary for the operation and performance of the App,
        such as:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Device model and operating system</li>
        <li>App version</li>
        <li>Advertising identifiers (if ads are enabled)</li>
        <li>Technical and performance data required for the App to function correctly</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This information cannot be used to identify you personally.
      </p>

      <h3>1.2. Personal information</h3>
      <p>
        The App does <strong>not</strong> collect any sensitive personal information such as:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Name, email address, phone number</li>
        <li>Contacts</li>
        <li>Photos or media</li>
        <li>Precise location data</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        However, third-party services used within the App may process certain information according to their own
        policies (see Section 3).
      </p>

      <h2>2. How We Use the Information</h2>
      <p>The information collected is used solely for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Ensuring the proper functionality of the App</li>
        <li>Improving performance, stability, and user experience</li>
        <li>Debugging errors and optimizing features</li>
        <li>Displaying advertising (if applicable)</li>
        <li>Processing in-app purchases</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do <strong>not</strong> sell or share personal information with third parties for commercial purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        Taptale may use third-party services that have their own privacy policies. These include, but are not limited
        to:
      </p>

      <h3>3.1. Google AdMob (if ads are enabled)</h3>
      <p>
        AdMob may collect device identifiers and advertising-related data. For more details, please refer to Google’s
        Privacy Policy:
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          https://policies.google.com/privacy
        </a>.
      </p>

      <h3>3.2. Google Play Billing</h3>
      <p>
        Google Play Billing is used to process in-app purchases. Google does not share personal purchasing information
        (such as full payment details) with the developer. For more information, visit:
        <a href="https://support.google.com/googleplay/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          https://support.google.com/googleplay/
        </a>.
      </p>

      <h3>3.3. Google Play Services</h3>
      <p>
        Google Play Services may be used for app performance, stability, and core functionality. For more details, see
        Google’s Privacy Policy:
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          https://policies.google.com/privacy
        </a>.
      </p>

      <!-- Si más adelante añades Play Games, solo duplica el bloque y ajusta el texto -->

      <h2>4. Data Storage</h2>
      <p>
        Taptale stores player data primarily <strong>locally on the device</strong>. Stored data may include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Game progress</li>
        <li>User settings</li>
        <li>Language preferences</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This information is not transmitted to our own external servers.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Security</h2>
      <p>
        We take reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect user information. However, no digital system
        is completely secure, and absolute protection cannot be guaranteed.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Children’s Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Taptale is not directed to children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children.
        If we become aware that information from a child under 13 has been collected, we will take steps to delete such
        data.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and the “Last
        updated” date at the top will be revised accordingly. We encourage you to review this Policy periodically.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or the App, you may contact us at:
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Email:</strong>
        <a href="mailto:milestone.artwork@gmail.com">milestone.artwork@gmail.com</a>
      </p>

